continent) have had a profound effect on these students, their families, and their communities of origin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aElectronic books. 0aMuslim college studentszNew HampshirezHanovervBiography. 0aMuslim youthxEducation (Higher)zNew HampshirezHanover. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aDiscrimination & Race Relations. 4aEducation & History Of Education.  aAdolescents.  aAmerican multiculturalism.  aArab American.  aAspiration.  aAssimilation.  aBelonging.  aIslamic Americans.  aIslamic Studies youth.  aIslamic Studies.  aIslamic youth.  aIslamophobia.  aMuslim American Experience after 9/11.  aMuslim American Experience.  aafter 9/11.  aamerican islam.  aamerican like me.  aamerican muslim studies.  aamerican racism.  aanti-racism.  aautobiography.  abooks about freshman.  achildren of immigrants.  acollege students.  acommon reading.  aessay anthologies.  aessays.  aethnic studies.  afreshman year reading.  aimmigrant Muslims.  aislamic social studies.  amuslim american history.  amuslim americans.  amuslim identity.  amuslim immigrants.  amuslim representation.  amuslim studies.  amuslim women in america.  amuslim youths in america.  amuslim.  amuslims in america.  anonfiction.  apost 9/11.  areligious prejudice.  axenophobia.  ayoung adult.  ayoung muslims.  ayouth culture.1 aGarrod, Andrew C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKilkenny, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPatel, Eboo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080147053040uhttps://www.degru